This paper discusses the development of natural language processing algorithms and the growth of conversational data, which are topics related to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on constructing a data-driven chatbot, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the use of online community posts as pseudo-conversational data, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
